cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a method for training neural networks that are robust to adversarial attacks, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses attacks and defenses, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach for training neural networks, which could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
